{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed98b005-6cdf-4e8d-8a9b-85b9ae4a6fcc","content":"Here are common options for creating a web API with authentication:\n\n**Templates:**\n- `dotnet new webapi` – ASP.NET Core Web API\n- `dotnet new webapi --use-controllers` – with controller-based pattern\n- `dotnet new web` – minimal API (lightweight)\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --name MyApi\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe483ede-86c2-4d72-86cc-98ac617a4a89","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/development question. Let me check if there's any relevant context in the current working directory first, but given the environment context says directory contents are unavailable and it's not a git repository, this seems like a general knowledge question.\n\nLet me answer based on my knowledge of common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":324,"requestId":"CFC9:9F1F0:11F9E3D:143BB0C:69F93E29"},"id":"7f905ee2-4d48-40a6-9156-d1f4cf7acff7","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:46.139Z","parentId":"6085da45-0554-4b19-9c48-30e481831580"}
